docs.abstract: Microsoft’s older operating system may not be the latest and greatest, but it’s officially supported for another few years.
docs.snippet: Microsoft’s older operating system may not be the latest and greatest, but it’s officially supported for another few years.
docs.lead_paragraph: Q. I am satisfied with Windows 7 and don’t wish to upgrade to Windows 10. Would a problem arise if I continue to use Windows 7, even after Microsoft stops sending updates for Windows 7?

docs.abstract: Microsoft intends to make sure the current version of Windows on your PC is always the newest version of its operating system.
docs.snippet: Microsoft intends to make sure the current version of Windows on your PC is always the newest version of its operating system.
docs.lead_paragraph: Q. Why does Windows always want to restart after it downloads updates? Do I have to restart? Why do some software updates not require the whole computer to be restarted?

headline.main: Why Windows 10 Wants to Automatically Restart

docs.abstract: An alliance of about 30 companies, including Microsoft and JPMorgan Chase, has plans to standardize data gathering and tracking with software that is seen as harder to hack.

docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Microsoft, JPMorgan Chase and other corporate giants are joining forces to create a new kind of computing system based on the virtual currency network Ethereum.

headline.main: Business Giants to Announce Creation of a Computing System Based on Ethereum
headline.print_headline: Companies Join to Build Blockchain Software

docs.abstract: System software updates — and upgrade problems — are not a Windows-only issue. Apple upgrades have caused disruptions for Mac users.

docs.lead_paragraph: Q. Microsoft seems to update Windows 10 constantly and it results in computer freezes and other issues for me. If I wanted to switch, is there a real advantage to Apple software as opposed to Microsoft?

docs.abstract: In a court filing, nearly 100 technology companies cited the “tremendous impact” of immigrants on the United States in opposing the Trump immigration ban.
docs.snippet: In a court filing, nearly 100 technology companies cited the “tremendous impact” of immigrants on the United States in opposing the Trump immigration ban.
docs.lead_paragraph: In late September, a group of tech leaders started a well-publicized effort to raise $100,000 for Hillary Clinton. In flush Silicon Valley, that is spare change. But by the time the election was over, the campaign had pulled in only $76,324.

headline.main: Tech Opposition to Trump Propelled by Employees, Not Executives
headline.print_headline: Tech Jumps Into Political Fray With a Push From Its Workers

docs.abstract: Microsoft’s service for keeping Windows current with the latest system patches can have problems, but troubleshooting might help those updates install.

docs.lead_paragraph: Q. Why is it that some Windows updates just refuse to install? In other words, when one goes into update history and it shows an update that has failed to install a number of times, what can you do?

headline.main: What to Do When Windows Updates Fail
